ce:section.ce:para:
Amino acid-modified GQDs were obtained by using an effective top-down route from the starting GO nanosheets. In a typical procedure, a strong ultrasonic peeling and prolonged thermal treatment can serve as scissors that cut the graphene into nanometer-sized colloid GQDs [31]. The carboxylic acid groups at the edges of the nanometer-sized GQDs were subsequently converted into acid chloride groups by using thionyl chloride. The acid chloride group, through a reaction with the amino group of amino acids, was then transformed into amino acid-modified GQDs (Scheme 1
                        ). TEM images of three kinds of GQDs were displayed in Fig. 1
                        . The TEM results demonstrated that the diameters of the synthesized GQDs are mainly distributed within the range of 3.0–6.2nm. The average diameter of AL-GQDs (Fig. 1G), AS-GQDs (Fig. 1H), and GL-GQDs (Fig. 1I), was approximately 4.5 (42%), 4.1 (31%), and 5.3nm (34%), respectively, indicating that the as-synthesized GQDs are highly monodispersed in aqueous solution. Furthermore, the high-resolution TEM images of an individual GQDs displayed typical hexagonal shape and zigzag edges (Figs. 1(D–F)), revealing that the GQDs are highly crystalline and consist of graphene units [32]. On the other hand, well-resolved lattice fringes can be clearly observed in high-resolution TEM images. For AL-GQDs and GL-GQDs, the lattice spacing are 0.285nm and 0.291nm, respectively, which are assigned to the (020) plane of graphitic carbon [33,34]. But for AS-GQDs, the lattice spacing is 0.225nm, which is assigned to the (100) facet of graphitic carbon [34,35]. It is worth mentioning that these lattice spacing are slightly larger than that reported in the literature [33–35], implying that the presence of amino acid functional groups can slightly enlarge the basal plane spacing of the GQDs [36].
